4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would exempt Sleep in Heavenly Peace,
6 Inc. from the payment of state sales and use taxes.
7 This bill would also allow municipalities and
8 counties to exempt this entity from local sales and use
9 taxes.
10
11
12 A BILL
13 TO BE ENTITLED
14 AN ACT
15
16 Relating to sales and use taxes; to exempt Sleep in
17 Heavenly Peace, Inc. from the payment of state, county and
18 municipal sales and use taxes.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
20 Section 1. (a) For the period commencing on October 1,
21 2026, and ending on September 30, 2029, Sleep in Heavenly
22 Peace, Inc. is exempt from paying state sales and use taxes.
23 (b) Sleep in Heavenly Peace, Inc. may be exempted from
24 paying county or municipal sales and use taxes upon approval
25 of the county or municipality pursuant to Section 40-23-4.01.
26 Section 2. This act shall become effective on September
27 1, 2026.
